a-size-base 3: Yo, fellow dog lovers! Just tossed my furry buddy one of these Dental Sticks, grain-free and chicken-flavored, from a 6.6-oz bag made for seniors, and let me tell you – it was an instant hit. This isn't just a treat; it's like a party for their taste buds and a high-five to their dental health.Firstly, the chicken flavor is legit. It's like these sticks have been seasoned with some kind of dog-approved magic. My old boy went for it like it was the best thing since belly rubs.The grain-free part is cool, especially if your pup's got a sensitive stomach. It's like they're keeping it healthy while still making it taste like a cheat day treat.Now, the dental aspect? Spot on. They're tough enough to give those chompers a good workout, helping to keep the tartar and plaque in check. It's like a gym session for their teeth, but way more fun.The size of the sticks is perfect for larger senior dogs. They’re substantial enough to keep them occupied but not too huge. It's like the perfect portion for a good munch without going overboard.And the bag? It's a decent size, meaning you're not running out after just a few treat sessions. It’s like having a ready stash of doggo happiness in your cupboard.

a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
a-size-base 3: I have bought the other varieties of Get Naked dental treats many times but this is the first time I have seen the senior large versions. The company uses very good ingredients including Dried potatoes, vegetable glycerin, gelatin, water, potato starch, chicken, natural chicken flavor, flaxseed, green lipped mussel, turmeric, cranberry fiber, calcium carbonate, parsley, l-ascorbyl-2 polyphosphate (source of vitamin C), chia seed, citric acid (preservative), fish oil (source of DHA). The large versions are about twice the size of the small version and suitable for my biggest dog or I could break them in half for my smaller guys.All of my dogs love these. They get either one or 1/2 a day depending on their size. They line up for one for their midmorning snack and can't wait to get them. Even my picky eater loves them. They are made in the US and I feel safe giving them to my dogs.

a-size-base 3: I’m always looking for grain free treats for my two rescues. I knew these sticks were large (about 6 inches each) but I figured I’d cut it in half and they could share one. Nope. I tried breaking it in two. My husband tried breaking it. We then tried cutting it. We could not cut it in half! So, I decided to let them each have one for a taste test. After a few minutes of gnawing, my old dog gave up and walked away. A few minutes later, my other dog yelped and dropped the stick. I think the hard ridge at the edge hit his gums causing pain so I took his away also. I’m giving two stars for ingredients and flavor but they were basically inedible by my dogs. I’d also be very careful of choking if your dog manages to bite off a small piece. A little softer and this could be a good product.
